

	 
       Train ride to sun set  Rustling sounds In a brisky cool mornings time Images flashing Past me in the window Rustling sounds Beneath me they shake Swerving out of control Falling into a lake Rustling sounds As we hit the icey cold water Losing breath Losing sight Rustling sounds Surrounding my body, entering my mind Head is throbbing Eyes go blind Rustling sounds Stomach churns Lungs close up The water burns Rustling sounds Words are a scream Gasping for breath It was all a bad dream. 
     
    
